# Setup Guide

## 1. Configure Your Router
- Change the default admin username and password.
- Enable WPA3 encryption for Wi-Fi.
- Disable remote management.

## 2. Set Up a Firewall
- Install pfSense on a dedicated device.
- Configure firewall rules to block unnecessary traffic.

## 3. Deploy IDS/IPS
- Install Snort or Suricata on a Raspberry Pi or old PC.
- Configure the IDS/IPS to monitor your network.

## 4. Monitor and Test
- Use Wireshark or Nagios to monitor network traffic.
- Simulate attacks using the scripts.
